packageMeta.name: purescript-nemo
packageMeta.description: Simple 2D game engine based on emoji.

declarations.comments:
Run game function for developing.
It short cuts startup view.
declarations.title: nemoDev

declarations.comments:
Game class.
Methods are called in order update, draw, sound every frame.
declarations.title: Game

declarations.comments:
Read class.
Read method is for parsing raw asset data.
declarations.title: Read

declarations.comments: Press state for watching press action.
declarations.title: PressState

declarations.comments: Update press state function for convenience.
declarations.title: updatePressState

declarations.comments:
Draw rotated emoji.
CAUTION: It does not display correctly (Deg = 45, 135, 225, 315).
declarations.title: emor

declarations.comments:
Draw mirrored rotated emoji.
CAUTION: It does not display correctly (Deg = 45, 135, 225, 315).
declarations.title: emor'

declarations.comments: Convert raw map string to emoji map
declarations.title: parseEmojiMap

declarations.comments: Convert raw sound string to sound
declarations.title: parseSound

declarations.comments: Play sound with given tone and bpm.
declarations.title: play

declarations.comments:
Asset type.
It contains map data and sound data.
declarations.title: Asset

declarations.comments:
Map collision detection.
Given emojis are treated as walls.
declarations.title: isMapCollide

declarations.comments:
Get map emoji with given indices.
Return Nothing there is not emoji.
declarations.title: getMapEmoji

declarations.comments:
Make asset data from raw maps and raw sounds.
If there are unparsable strings, exception raised when executing javascript.
declarations.title: mkAsset

declarations.comments: Collision detection if an object protrudes out of monitor
declarations.title: isMonitorCollide

declarations.comments: Collision detection if an object completely protrudes out of monitor
